                  {
                    "value": "Bar charts can be used when comparing quantities across categories for a single metric (such as sales) or to compare two or three metrics (such as sales and target); they can be used to show trends over time if the data points are discrete (such as monthly, yearly); or for displaying rank or order based on alpha/numeric order or ascending/descending on the metric; they are also a good candidate for showing parts of a whole where there are too many categories for a pie or donut chart.",
